Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.23,1:26:09.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,非常感謝你們的招待\N{\rENG}Thank you for a wonderful lunch. it was delicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.00,1:26:15.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你怎麼看壟斷\N{\rENG}What do you think of monopolies?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.54,1:26:17.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你怎麼看\N{\rENG}You mean like the game?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.84,1:26:21.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得壟斷不太好\N{\rENG}No, I just think monopolies were made illegal in the country, frank,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.57,1:26:23.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,那樣就失去競爭了\N{\rENG}Cause nobody wants to compete, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.91,1:26:26.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人願意和一個壟斷集團競爭\N{\rENG}Nobody wants to compete, not with a monopoly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.05,1:26:29.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你讓那些牛奶農場去競爭\N{\rENG}I mean, you let the dairy farmers do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.75,1:26:31.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,第二天肯定會有一半人已經破產了了\N{\rENG}Half of them would be out of business tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.88,1:26:33.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒辦法  都是為了討生活\N{\rENG}Just trying to make a living.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.45,1:26:35.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是你的權利  我是說\N{\rENG}That's your right, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.35,1:26:38.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,人人都有權利去選擇怎麼生活  這就是美國\N{\rENG}It's everyone's right. it's America.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.39,1:26:42.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們只是不能太霸道了  得給別人留條活路\N{\rENG}We just can't do it at the unreasonable expense of others.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.93,1:26:45.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,不然就會變得不美國了\N{\rENG}Cause then it becomes un-American.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.13,1:26:47.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼一加侖牛奶的價格\N{\rENG}That's why the price we pay for that gallon of milk
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.23,1:26:49.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,總是不會和它的實際生產成本一樣\N{\rENG}Could never represent the true cost of production
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.10,1:26:53.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為價格必須有人來制定和控制  這樣才對大家都公平\N{\rENG}Cause it's got to be controlled. it's gotta be set. it's gotta be fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.71,1:26:56.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,有誰來控制?  我覺得自己定的價格就很公平\N{\rENG}Gotta be controlled by who? I set a price that I think is fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.31,1:26:57.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,-我不覺得那樣公平  -你覺得不公平?\N{\rENG}I don't think it's fair. you don't?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.71,1:26:59.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,-我不覺得那樣公平  -可我覺得公平\N{\rENG}I don't think it's fair. I think it's fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.28,1:27:01.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道  消費者對你的貨很滿意\N{\rENG}I mean, I know your customers are happy, frank,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.38,1:27:04.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,但他們不過是群癮君子而已\N{\rENG}Bunch of fucking junkies that they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.22,1:27:08.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你得也為那些擠奶工們想想  你為我們想過嗎\N{\rENG}But we fellow dairy farmers out here, frank, are you thinking of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.42,1:27:10.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,你為他們考慮過嗎\N{\rENG}You thinking of them?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.29,1:27:12.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,-擠奶工  -對\N{\rENG}The dairy farmers? yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.43,1:27:18.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,多明尼克  他們也沒為我著想過啊\N{\rENG}I'm thinking of them, dominic, about as much as they've ever thought about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.30,1:27:20.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,行  先不扯這個了\N{\rENG}I'm just thinking out loud now.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.13,1:27:23.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你把一部分貨拿出來\N{\rENG}If you took some of your inventory, frank,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.94,1:27:26.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,批發給其他人\N{\rENG}And you sold it wholesale...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.47,1:27:28.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,先坐\N{\rENG}Sit.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.54,1:27:33.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們能合作  我們來分銷\N{\rENG}We could work. we could do some distribution.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.25,1:27:35.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道怎麼合作  我現在就做得挺好的\N{\rENG}I don't know. I'm pretty good, dominic.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.58,1:27:39.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我佔有110街  155街  我足夠了\N{\rENG}You know, I got 110th, 155th, river to river. I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.62,1:27:42.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是說我們一起把它做大\N{\rENG}That's kind of a mom and pop store next to what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.66,1:27:44.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,把它推向整個市場\N{\rENG}I mean, let's go at least bigger than kmart.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.39,1:27:49.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,洛杉磯  底特律  拉斯維加斯  把貨推向全國市場\N{\rENG}I'm talking about la, chicago, detroit, las vegas. let's go nationwide, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.76,1:27:54.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我絕對保證你的安全  那不正是你想要的嗎\N{\rENG}I'm gonna guarantee you your peace of mind here. you don't want that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.52,1:27:57.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,你需要它\N{\rENG}You're going to need it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.82,1:27:59.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道你怎麼看我\N{\rENG}I don't know how you view me, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.56,1:28:01.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我是個有修養的人  弗蘭克\N{\rENG}I'm kind of a renaissance man, frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.52,1:28:03.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我每天打交道的那些人\N{\rENG}You know, the people I deal with on a daily basis,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.66,1:28:05.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,甚至都不是文明人\N{\rENG}You know, they're not enlightened, frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.56,1:28:08.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你跟他們說公民權如同對牛彈琴\N{\rENG}You talk to them about civil rights, they don't know, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.43,1:28:09.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,而且他們不喜歡改變\N{\rENG}They're not open to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.23,1:28:13.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,總是按傳統和老規矩辦事  一直都是這樣\N{\rENG}Not from the way things are done and who's doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.87,1:28:17.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是如果我跟他們說一聲就不會有什麼誤會\N{\rENG}I talk to them, there's just no misunderstandings.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.58,1:28:21.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是我能給你提供的安全\N{\rENG}And that's what I mean by your peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.25,1:28:29.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,你現在進貨價格是多少?  七萬五  八萬美金一公斤?\N{\rENG}You're paying, what, $75,000, $80,000 a kilo?
